        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>LAW OFFICES OF<lb/>
                M. S. &#38; I. S. ISAACS&#44;<lb/>
                115 BROADWAY&#44; &#40;BOREEL BUILDING&#44;&#41;<lb/>
                NEW YORK.<lb/></p>
            <p>Oct. 19&#47;88<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr Goldman &#38; I<lb/> spent the day at Carmel&#44;<lb/> had lengthy interviews with<lb/> Mr Miller and some of the<lb/> colonists.  Mr Miller made<lb/> a liberal concession and<lb/> we took his proposition in<lb/> writing.  The other land owners<lb/> we could not see&#44; but shall<lb/> hear from them early next<lb/> week.  Meanwhile&#44; I am<lb/> able to report that with<lb/> the amount appropriated&#44; all<lb/> the original colonists who survive<lb/> and all the others who need it<lb/> &#40;except perhaps the single men&#41;<lb/> can be comfortably established<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>with land <hi rend="underline">paid for</hi> in most<lb/> instances and house partly<lb/> paid for&#44; but entirely within<lb/> their ability to take care of<lb/></p>
            <p>I would advise the deposit<lb/> of the draft in a Phila.<lb/> bank or trust company&#44; so<lb/> as to be in a position to draw<lb/> against it&#44; when you are<lb/> ready &#40;after Mr Sulzberger&#39;s<lb/> ex<hi rend="sup">m</hi>.&#41; to pay for the land.<lb/></p>
            <p>Truly Yours<lb/>
                M S Isaacs<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr Goldman &#38; I will prepare<lb/> a detailed report from the<lb/> data obtained or verified<lb/> yesterday.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
